title.narrative: IR 3.4: CORE COMMITMENTS ON CHILD PROTEC

description.narrative: IR 3.4: Relevant Core Commitments on Child Protection are met in all humanitarian settings, which contributes to Child Protection And Emergencies, Prevention And Response Services For Violence Against Children. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: PCR 3. National institutions incorporate the CRC and other child-related international conventions into their improved legal and operational protection frameworks and services including combating GBV and VAC violence in schools and Juvenile Justice
